I can't really comment on the changes because I'm very unfamiliar with the newly introduced class.

The test method can be simplified:
{noformat}
	    try {
	      createQueue("root.a.a-auto.a2-auto.a3-auto");
	      Assert.fail("Queue creation should not succeed because the distance " +
	          "from the first static parent is above limit");
	    } catch (SchedulerDynamicEditException ignored) {
	
	    }
{noformat}

Instead of the try-catch block, just use {{@Test(expected = SchedulerDynamicEditException.class)}} and remove the assertion.

